Template_FlogrThumbs - A mash-up of "flogr" and "LightBox 2"

What it does:

Inside your existing mediawiki installation it allows you to...

* show a list of thumbnails of a given flickr set
* display set title and the amount of pictures
* open big version of the pictures in an overlay on click
* browse through the set inside the open overlay

Requirements:

* installed flogr extension
* installed lightbox extension

Setup:

* create "FlogrThumbs" template (copy content of the Template_FlogrThumbs file into /wiki/Template:FlogrThumbs?action=edit of your wiki)
* style information (copy from FlogrThumbs.css into your wiki's skin's CSS file)

Usage:

To embed the list of thumbnails inside an article, put the template tag
  {{FlogrThumbs|<flickr_set_id>}}
at the desired position inside the wiki syntax.


Original Projects:
* http://code.google.com/p/flogr/
* http://lokeshdhakar.com/projects/lightbox2/

